title: Material Redesign
message:
Material Redesign

After numerous users beta testing the app, I realized the original design
was hardly intuitive, and not very visually appealing. I took the
opportunity to redesign the data entry and implemented Google's Material
Design.

title: Redesign for better visual appeal
message:
Redesign for better visual appeal

Also incorporated some HTML in order to single out the price in a total
statement, and highlight it red.

title: Change text width to 120
message:
Change text width to 120

Android and Java are too verbose to be constricted to 100 characters.
Mainly a reformatting commit.

title: Extract string resources
message:
Extract string resources

Not using string resources is a bad idea. Also concatenating strings for a
textview was ill-advised; String.format() was a better recommended option.
One refactor as well.

title: Reformat app into two activities.
message:
Reformat app into two activities.

Initial design was poor, the app is much cleaner using two activities
rather than bunching it all onto a scrollscreen activity.

title: Add savings display feature
message:
Add savings display feature

This patch will be able to show the user how much money they save compared
to alternate types of metrocards they could have purchased. Also include
some light touches to the UI, making some elements clearer.

title: Improve UI for value entry
message:
